   a. "Uncommitted funds" is CBO's term for the surpluses that remain each
   year after paying down publicly held debt available for redemption. CBO
   assumes that those funds, which accumulate from one year to the next,
   earn proceeds at a rate equal to the average interest rate projected
   for Treasury bills and notes.
   b. As a percentage of total GDP over the 10-year period.
