   SOURCE: Congressional Budget Office.
   NOTES: In CBO's projections, discretionary outlays are always higher
   than discretionary budget authority because of spending from the
   Highway Trust Fund and the Airport and Airways Trust Fund, which is
   subject to obligation limitations in appropriation acts. The budget
   authority for such programs is provided in authorizing legislation and
   is not considered discretionary. Another reason that outlays exceed
   budget authority is that outlays include spending from appropriations
   provided in previous years.
   Numbers in this table include spending from the 2001 Supplemental
   Appropriations Act (P.L. 107-20) and the continuation of such spending
   through 2011.
